META AD COPY RULES
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

PRIMARY TEXT  (≤ 125 characters — this is the mobile feed cutoff before "See More")
  • Open with a pattern interrupt or curiosity gap in the very first line
  • Root the hook in the specific opening and closing beat of this clip
  • Use the structural contrast to create a "wait, how?" moment
  • Do not spoil the resolution
  • Do not use ALL CAPS, excessive punctuation, or emoji
  • Do not name the drama title — let the story hook sell itself
  • Tone: conversational, scroll-stopping, present tense preferred

HEADLINE  (≤ 27 characters — appears below the video thumbnail)
  • One sharp phrase that names the dramatic stakes, not the plot
  • Avoid generic labels like "Episode 1" or "Watch Now"
  • Examples of good headlines: "She Knew Too Much", "He Came Back Different"

DESCRIPTION  (≤ 27 characters — optional line below the headline)
  • Complement the headline — do not repeat it
  • Can name a character, a location, or a situation fragment
  • Acceptable to leave as a short CTA if nothing better fits: "Watch free"

ABSOLUTE PROHIBITION:
  ✗ No clickbait superlatives ("You won't believe", "Shocking", "OMG")
  ✗ No explicit spoilers of outcomes or resolutions
  ✗ primary_text must be a single paragraph — no line breaks

